üü¶ EPIC ‚Äî Hardware Allocation Process

(User entry: Collect My Equipment)

Goal

Allow a technician to allocate hardware to a collaborator only based on an existing request, with full traceability, management context visibility, and controlled delivery.

‚∏ª

üß≠ PHASE 1 ‚Äî Identify the equipment owner

‚∏ª

US1 ‚Äî Start Hardware Allocation Process from visit management

As a technician
I want to start the Hardware Allocation Process when managing a visitor
So that I can deliver requested equipment

Acceptance Criteria
	‚Ä¢	The process is available only for visits of type Collect My Equipment
	‚Ä¢	The process starts when the technician clicks Manage
	‚Ä¢	The process name displayed is Hardware Allocation Process
	‚Ä¢	The process uses the same layout/stepper pattern as Return Hardware

‚∏ª

US2 ‚Äî Ask if the pickup is for the visitor or another collaborator

As a technician
I want to confirm whether the equipment pickup is for the visitor or another collaborator
So that I retrieve the correct pending requests

Acceptance Criteria

WHEN the process starts
THEN a question is displayed: ‚ÄúIs the equipment pickup for you?‚Äù
AND buttons Yes / No are available

WHEN I click Yes
THEN the visitor is considered as the equipment owner

WHEN I click No
THEN I am redirected to the collaborator search screen


‚∏ª

US3 ‚Äî Search and select the target collaborator

